headlines.description: — The Minnesota Timberwolves refused to let one road loss become a streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Timberwolves beat Heat 113-104 for 7th win in 8 games

headlines.description: — Alex Caruso returned to the rotation, and the Chicago Bulls went back to their disruptive ways.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan, Vucevic lead Bulls to 101-91 win over Cavaliers

events.name: Indiana Pacers at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton had 19 points and 10 assists and the Indiana Pacers snapped a three-game skid, beating the San Antonio Spurs 119-108 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Haliburton helps Pacers snap skid with win over Spurs

events.name: Milwaukee Bucks at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Klay Thompson has been waiting for his shot to start falling consistently, and he certainly found a groove for Golden State against defending champion Milwaukee.
headlines.shortLinkText: Klay Thompson scores season-high 38, Warriors top Bucks

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam scored 33 points, Scottie Barnes had 25 and the Toronto Raptors pulled away late to beat the Denver Nuggets 127-115 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Siakam scores 33 points, Raptors beat the Nuggets 127-115

headlines.description: — Playing without Rudy Gobert and Mike Conley, Utah Jazz coach Quin Snyder called it a “man-up type of game.”
headlines.shortLinkText: Clarkson has career-high 45 points to lift Jazz past Kings

events.name: Washington Wizards at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Josh Hart scored a career-high 44 points, helping the Portland Trail Blazers end a six-game skid with a 127-118 victory over the Washington Wizards on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hart scores 44 as Trail Blazers top Wizards, end 6-game skid
